Data: Hello and welcome to Cricinfo's coverage of Australia's tour of New Zealand, which begins with today's Twenty20 in Wellington. The news at the Westpac Stadium is that Daniel Vettori has won the toss and New Zealand will bat.
Tait to McCullum, 2 runs 150 km/h Tait angles into McCullum's pads and he clips it to long leg for a couple. Quick outfield.
Tait to McCullum, no run 153 km/h bouncer from Tait and McCullum is easily out of the way as he ducks
Tait to McCullum, no run 153 km/h good channel from Tait and McCullum pushes away from his body and misses

Tait to McCullum, OUT This one is quick again and McCullum pushes away from his body and it takes the outside edge and Haddin takes a remarkable catch diving full stretch to his right, snaring the ball in one hand. What a start!
Tait to Guptill, no run 153 km/h bouncer again from Tait to welcome Guptill to the crease and he ducks underneath
Tait to Guptill, no run 150 km/h good channel from Tait and Guptill allows it through to the keeper
Nannes to Ingram, 1 run 147 km/h good start from Nannes as he bends his back and Ingram punches off the back foot to third man
Nannes to Guptill, no run 147 kph angled down the leg side and not called wide. It may have taken he pad on the way through.
Nannes to Guptill, no run 147 kph, good line and length, shouldered arms through to the keeper
Nannes to Guptill, no run 149 kph, a touch fuller this time and Guptill tries to play a square drive but misses
Nannes to Guptill, FOUR runs 147 kph, good length but too wide from Nannes and Guptill drives on the up through extra cover
Nannes to Guptill, no run 149 kph, good channel from Nannes and allowed through to the keeper
Tait to Ingram, no run 150 kph, back of a length and Ingram drives off the back foot from the toes of the bat to cover point
Tait to Ingram, no run 149 kph, angled into his pads and Ingram whips it straight to square leg and Christian whips it to the bowlers end. Sharp from Christian.
Tait to Ingram, no run 153 kph, quick and short and Ingram is stringly in behind it and defending
Tait to Ingram, no run 155 kph, this one is short and rapid! Ingram goes inside the line comfortably, well played.
Tait to Ingram, no run 150 kph, another bouncer from Tait angled down leg and Ingram ducks underneath
Tait to Ingram, 1 run 153 kph, good channel and Ingram swings it off the outside edge to third man
Nannes to Ingram, no run 150 kph, offers some width and Ingram back foot drives to point off the outside edge
Nannes to Ingram, 1 bye 150 kph, short and quick from Nannes as Ingram attempts to pull but misses and Haddin does well to get a glove on it
Nannes to Guptill, no run 148 kph, back of a length and Guptill defends with soft hands behind the wicket
Nannes to Guptill, no run 150 kph, back of a length played to backward point
Nannes to Guptill, FOUR runs 148 kph, full on middle and leg and Guptill whips it through mid wicket for four
Nannes to Guptill, no run 151 kph, good length angled across Guptill and he plays and misses
Johnson to Ingram, OUT 143 kph, great start from Johnson as he bowls back of a length and Ingram plays all around it trying to work it through the leg side and it takes out middle stump
Johnson to Taylor, no run 146 kph, full and wide and Taylor looks to play a square drive but misses
Johnson to Taylor, no run 149 kph, good length from Johnson and Taylor hangs the bat out to dry. Almost looks as if he didn't pick that one up.
Johnson to Taylor, FOUR runs 149 kph, shorter from Johnson angled into Taylor's ribs and he works it fine off his glove for four. Haddin was close to catching that as he stuck out his left mit.
Johnson to Taylor, 1 run 148 kph, good length and Taylor goes back and works it to mid wicket for a single
Johnson to Guptill, no run 150 kph, Guptill plays it to point and there's a slight mix up as Clarke hits the stumps at the strikers end and Guptill is home safe
Nannes to Taylor, no run Taylor pushes to point and set off for the run, Guptill makes a late 'no' call and Clarke trhows at the strikers end but misses. Taylor was long gone!
Nannes to Taylor, 1 run back of a length and Taylor works it into the leg side and they take a sharp single
Nannes to Guptill, FOUR runs too short and Guptill is onto it quickly and pulls over mid wicket for four. Good stroke
Nannes to Guptill, no run fuller on leg stump and Guptill pushes nicely to mid on
Nannes to Guptill, FOUR runs short again and it hurries Guptill on the pull, taking the splice of the bat but it's once bounce four on these short boundaries
Nannes to Guptill, 2 runs short and wide and he back cuts to third man where Tait bobbles it and they have enough time for an easy two
Johnson to Taylor, 1 run full on off stump and driven to deep point
Johnson to Guptill, 1 run good length from Johnson, a fraction straight and Guptill is back and defending with soft hands into the off side and they take a quick single
Johnson to Taylor, 2 runs short and pulled from high on the bat forwrad of square for a couple to the sweeper on the leg side

Johnson to Taylor, OUT Taylor walks across to the off side and looks to heave it over mid wicket but he misses and it takes him on his back foot outside the line of off stump and he's given out LBW. The hosts certainly didn't need that and Australia are
Johnson to Franklin, 1 run waist high full toss and Franklin works it to deep square leg
Johnson to Guptill, no run good length as Guptill tries to play to third man but misses. Well bowled
Smith to Franklin, 1 run full and driven to long off
Smith to Guptill, no run full and Guptill moves back and cuts to short third man
Smith to Guptill, 1 run uses his feet and drives to the off side sweeper
Smith to Franklin, no run good length from SMith and Franklin pushes back to the bowler
Smith to Franklin, no run wrong'un from Smith and Franklin plays back down the pitch
Smith to Franklin, 1 run shorter this time and Franklin pushes to long on
Hussey to Franklin, 2 runs chipped over extra cover for a couple
Hussey to Franklin, 1 run played to long on
Hussey to Guptill, 1 run played nicely to the point boundary
Hussey to Franklin, no run played back to the bowler
Hussey to Franklin, 1 run yorker squeezed to mid wicket for a single
Hussey to Guptill, 1 run driven to long on
Smith to Guptill, 1 run driven aerially to long off
Smith to Franklin, no run played to mid wicket where Clarke fields well to save a run
Smith to Franklin, 1 run uses his feet and chips to long on
Smith to Guptill, no run played back to the bowler
Smith to Guptill, 2 runs chipped over the bowler, hit rather well and Hussey dives in the deep to save four
Smith to Guptill, 2 runs lapped fine for a couple
Johnson to Franklin, 1 run good length played to backward point
Johnson to Guptill, 2 runs droppedgood length and Guptill pulls off the top edge. Haddin moves well towards square leg and puts it down!
Johnson to Guptill, 1 run played to deep square leg for a single
Johnson to Franklin, 1 run worked into the off side for a sharp single
Johnson to Guptill, OUT short and Guptill pulls into mid wicket where Watson moves back from mid wicket and takes the catch half-way between the boundary and the 30m circle
Johnson to Franklin, no run angled into the pads and played to mid wicket off the pad
Watson to Hopkins, no run mistimes the cut to the off side.
Watson to Hopkins, 1 run moves forward and drives to the sweeper cover for a single.
Watson to Franklin, 1 run fuller and driven down the ground to long on.
Watson to Hopkins, 1 run short ball and pulled well to deep backward square leg and picks up a single, fielded by Johnson.
Watson to Franklin, no run not short for the pull, he goes for it and gets beaten, goes over the stumps to the keeper.
Watson to Franklin, 1 run hit in the air down the ground and one bounce to the fielder at long on, single taken.
Johnson to Franklin, no run back of a length and timed nicely back at Johnson who parries it to cover
Johnson to Franklin, no run short and wide and Franklin tries to cut but misses
Johnson to Franklin, 2 runs half volley and Franklin hits it straight back over the bowler's head for a couple to long on
Johnson to Franklin, no run bouncer from Johnson and Franklin ducks underneath thinking it may well be a wide but not to be
Johnson to Franklin, 1 leg bye fullish angled into leg and Franklin tries to whip it over the leg side but it takes him on the back leg
Johnson to Oram, 1 wide full and angled down the leg side, only just misses the leg stump
Johnson to Oram, 1 run full and worked into mid wicket for an easy single
Nannes to Oram, OUT short and angled at the body and Oram pulls to mid wicket where Watson dives full stretch to his right and pulls of a superb one handed grab!
Nannes to McCullum, 1 run short and cut off the outside edge to third man
Nannes to Franklin, no run driven to mid off who is inside the circle
Nannes to Franklin, no run another bouncer and Franklin ducks underneath
Nannes to Franklin, 1 run half volley driven to mid off. This is turning out to be a great over from the former ski instructor
Nannes to McCullum, OUT good length from Nannes, McCullum tries to pull, it takes him high on the bat and it loops to Hussey at mid on
Christian to Franklin, 1 run full and worked off the inside edge to the leg side sweeper
Christian to Hopkins, 1 run full and whipped off leg stump to fine leg
Christian to Franklin, 1 run Dropped smashed straight back to the bowler, Christian throws a hand at it and they take one
Christian to Hopkins, FOUR runs gives himself room and square drives on one knee over cover. Super shot!
Christian to Hopkins, 1 run good length and pulled off the inside edge to fine leg
Christian to Franklin, SIX runs half volley on leg stump and Franklin helps it on its way over square leg for half a dozen
Watson to Hopkins, no run DROPPED slower ball which he tries to hit over the top but he hits it straight to Clarke who puts it down
Watson to Hopkins, 1 run attempts to drive, it takes the inside edge and falls into the off side
Watson to Franklin, no run short ball and Franklin goes underneath
Watson to Franklin, 1 run back of a length and driven neatly to long on
Watson to Hopkins, 1 run steps across to off stump and tries to heave it over the leg side but gets an edge into the off side
Watson to Franklin, SIX runs short and Franklin sees it early and pulls over square leg for a maximum
Tait to Franklin, no run full and wide and Franklin doesn't show any footwork to get closer to the ball and he misses well outside off just inside the wide line
Tait to Franklin, 1 run yorker squeezed out to point where Clarke misfields and they take one
Tait to Vettori, 1 bye good length beats Vettori for pace and it goes over the top of middle stump and Haddin can't glove it cleanly
Tait to Franklin, OUT full delivery and Franklin drives down the ground in the air, he mistimes it and Smith dives forward to his left at mid off to take a good catch
Tait to Vettori, no run steps away to the off side and actually gives himself too much room missing the ball it it goes just past the off stump
Tait to Vettori, 1 run yorker played to the squarer of two third man fielders
Watson to Vettori, 1 run steps away to leg this time and swats it to long on
Watson to Tuffey, 1 bye slower ball and Tuffey plays far too early, it bounces just over middle stump and Haddin cannot clean up behind the stumps
Watson to Vettori, 1 run good length and Vettori tries to swing it over the leg side but mistimes it to long off

Watson to Tuffey, OUT Tuffey swings hard again and misses, Vettori calls him through for a bye, Haddin rolls to collect the ball as it bounces in front of him and he throws down the stumps in the same motion. Superb work from the keeper!
Watson to Bond, 1 run mistimed drive to long on
Watson to Tuffey, OUT Tuffey moves across to outside off stump and it takes him on the thigh pad and Haddin collects it and half-appeals and umpire Baxter gives it out! Unlucky for Tuffey there
Join us in 10 minutes as Australia begin their chase, needing just 119 to win.
The players now take their tea. I suspect it will taste a lot better for the Australian's who shocked the hosts with genuine pace up front and they were never able to recover.

That is a poor display from the hosts and Australia were rather hot and cold in the field, taking a couple of very goodgrabs, while also putting down a couple. Clarke had a difficult time with a couple of misfields too.
This is Marc Ellison signing off. Goodluck and god speed.

We look ahead to Sunday now where the series moves to Christchurch for the second and final T20 international. Thanks for joining us here for live coverage of tonights match. Please join us again at 1400 NZDST or 0200 GMT on Sunday.

Mitchell Johnson is named Man of the Match for his three for 19 off four overs. He picked up the wickets of Ingram, Taylor and Guptill which dented any momentum New Zealand would've hoped for up front.

Clarke is ecstatic with his pacemen and the batting form of Warner and Watson. He feels the team are hungry to be here in New Zealand and with everyone competing for spots, he feels his side stands in good stead looking forward.
Vettori is confident his side can get it right for the next match in Christchurch on Sunday but isn't looking forward to bowling with the short boundaries straight down the ground.

Australia's reply never looked in doubt with Warner and Watson getting away to a flier before Bond and Vettori pegged it back. Hussey struck a neat 46 while captain Clarke worked the ball into the gaps without taking too many risks to finish 18 not out.

New Zealand were undone by the pace of Tait, Nannes and Johnson atth top of the innings and were chasing their tails as a result for the rest of the innings, eventually being bowled out for 118 from the final ball fo the innings.

David Hussey is happy with his team's effort and enjoyed the pace in the wicket which allowed him to score 46 off 36 balls. He hit nicely over the top straight down the ground and pulled strongly whenever the bowlers dropped short.
Australia just far too good for New Zealand tonight, winning by six wickets with 24 balls to spare.
Bond to Warner, no run back of a length and Warner pushes to mid on where Vettori's presence prevents the single
Bond to Warner, no run superb delivery swinging away from Warner and he plays and misses
Bond to Warner, 3 runs good length but chipped back over the bowlers' head. He didn't quite time it well enough and it stops just inside the rope
Bond to Watson, no run back of a length and Watson is in behind it and defending back to the bowler
Bond to Watson, 1 run fuller on off stump and he drives off the inside edge to mid wicket
Bond to Warner, SIX runs decent length but too straight and Warner picks it up over square leg for half a dozen!
Tuffey to Watson, no run full on middle stump and he drives powerfully to mid on
Tuffey to Watson, FOUR runs good length but a fraction too straight and he pulls past Brendon McCullum through mid wicket for four
Tuffey to Watson, FOUR runs full again and he plays a nice lofted drive over mid on which bounces just short of the ropes for four
Tuffey to Watson, FOUR runs good length but just enough width for Watson to free his arms and hit through extra cover for four. Outstanding stroke on the up!
Tuffey to Watson, 2 runs slower ball and Watson hits it high over mid off, Oram moves backwards but can't get back quickly enough to get under it and it bounces just outside of his reach
Tuffey to Watson, FOUR runs shorter this time and he pulls off the top edge over first slip for four
Bond to Warner, FOUR runs full and he leans back and hammers it over long on
Bond to Warner, no run better length and he leans back again but mistimes it back to Bond
Bond to Warner, FOUR runs good length on off stump and Warner steps away to leg and crunches it through cover for four. What timing from the wee man.
Bond to Warner, no run fuller and crunched to Guptill at point
Bond to Warner, 2 runs dropped Warner tries to heave it over the leg side and it takes the edge and flies high Taylor's right at first slip, he throws out a hand but can't hold onto it
Vettori to Watson, no run short and slow and cut to point
Vettori to Watson, no run shortish and slow and driven to mid off
Vettori to Watson, no run flatter this time and he looks to cut and gets a bottom edge onto the keepers pads
Vettori to Johnson, 1 run flatter and Johnson moves back and works it into the leg side
Vettori to Clarke, no run tossed up and Clarke uses his feet and defends back to Vettori. Clarke just has so much time
Bond to Johnson, no run back of a length and Johnson pushes back down the track
Bond to Hussey, 1 wide well wide down the leg side
Bond to Hussey, no run short and Hussey 'gives himself room' and plays to point
Bond to Hussey, no run back of a length on middle and Hussey is back and defending
Bond to Hussey, 3 runs good length lofted over cover and the fieldsmen do well in tandem to save the boundary
Bond to Clarke, no run good length on middle stump and Clarke defends into the off side
Vettori to Hussey, no run flat this time and played off the back foot to point
Vettori to Hussey, no run angled into the stumps from around the wicket and Hussey closes the face and it takes the outside edge and bounces in front of backward point
Vettori to Hussey, no run flatter again and Hussey defends into the off side
Vettori to Hussey, 1 run tossed up and Hussey uses the crease well to cut to point where Nathan McCullum misfields
Vettori to Clarke, 1 run tossed up and worked into the leg side for a quick single
Vettori to Hussey, 2 runs short and pulled out to deep forward square for a couple as Ingram misfields
Tuffey to Clarke, no run full and Clarke mistimes the drive off the outside edge to backward point
Tuffey to Clarke, 1 run good length on off and driven off the inside half of the blade to mid on
Tuffey to Hussey, 2 runs short and pulled over mid wicket for a couple to Ingram, the leg side sweeper
Tuffey to Hussey, FOUR runs half volley cracked over mid off for four, super stroke
Tuffey to Hussey, 1 run good channel from Tuffey and Hussey pushes to point where Nathan McCullum misfields
Tuffey to Clarke, 1 run good length and Clarke plays it through mid wicket to Ingram, sweeping on the leg side
Oram to Clarke, no run slower ball bouncer and Clarke pulls off the glove but it bounces just short of keeper Hopkins
Oram to Clarke, no run good length worked into the leg side and mid wicket dives to save a run
Oram to Clarke, 1 run back of a length whipped off his hip to square leg for a single
Oram to Hussey, 1 run good channel but just enough width to guide to third man
Oram to Clarke, FOUR runs short and pulled strongly through mid wicket past the hands of Taylor for four. Elegant stroke
Oram to Clarke, no run played and missed outside the off stump
McCullum to Hussey, 1 run short and pulled behind square to the sweeper
McCullum to Clarke, 1 run flat again and punched off the back shoe to long on
McCullum to Hussey, 2 runs short and pulled again through square leg for a couple right on the fence
McCullum to Hussey, 1 run full and driven sweetly to long on
McCullum to Clarke, 1 run tossed up, Clarke comes down the pitch and drives to long on
McCullum to Hussey, no run short and cut to Franklin who dives at point to save four
Oram to Clarke, 1 run back of a length and pushed into the off side for an easy single
Oram to Hussey, FOUR runs short and pulled sweetly over mid wicket. It bounces just inside the rope.

Oram to Hussey, 2 runs short agai and pulled behind square for a couple. The throw from the deep is good. Hopkins takes the ball in front of the stumps and whips off the bails. Hussey is found to be home safe. The question is - would it have hit the stu
Oram to Hussey, no run driven firmly to mid off
Oram to Hussey, 1 run good length and guided to third man
Oram to Clarke, 1 wide bouncer down leg and called wide
Oram to Clarke, no run good length worked into the leg side for a single
McCullum to Hussey, no run goes back to a fuller one and defends into the off side
McCullum to Hussey, FOUR runs tossed up and Hussey lofts it over mid off gloriously for four
McCullum to Hussey, FOUR runs short and pulled through backward square leg to the leg side sweeper, Tuffey, who misfields diving at full stretch
McCullum to Hussey, FOUR runs this one is slower but short and pulled behind square leg for four, beating Oram at fine leg
McCullum to Hussey, 1 run moves back and guides to backward point
McCullum to Clarke, no run uses his feet and drives back to the bowler who throws it back and hits Clarke on the back of the leg
Vettori to Hussey, 1 run short and cut to the off side sweeper
Vettori to Clarke, no run short again and cut to short cover
Vettori to Clarke, 1 wide Clarke uses his feet and it angles dow leg, it yorks Hopkins and he misses a difficult stumping
Vettori to Clarke, 1 run advances down the track again (what confidence!) and drives to long off
Vettori to Hussey, 1 run short and pulled to deep mid wicket
Vettori to Clarke, no run short and cut to cover
Vettori to Clarke, 1 run comes down the track again and pushes to long on
Bond to Clarke, 1 run back of a length in at the body and whipped off his hip to fine leg
Bond to Hussey, no run back of a length and defended into the off side
Bond to Hussey, 1 run short in at the body and Hussey is back and fending into the leg side
Bond to Clarke, no run yorker played to cover
Bond to Clarke, 1 wide angled down the leg side. Bond just falling over slightly in his action
Bond to Clarke, 1 wide once again down the leg side. An action replay from the ball before
Bond to Clarke, 1 run short and in at the body and Clarke works it into the leg side with soft hands
Bond to Hussey, 3 runs slightly slower from Bond this time and Hussey drives it straight back over his head. He doesn't quite time it well enough to get four
Vettori to Hussey, no run tossed up and Hussey tries to cut but misses
Vettori to Hussey, no run flatter and pushed into the off side as Clarke sends him back
Vettori to Hussey, no run short and played to short third man
Vettori to Hussey, 1 run shortish and cut hard to deep point
Vettori to Clarke, 1 run full and angled into leg and pushed to long on
Vettori to Hussey, 1 run half volley pushed to long off
McCullum to White, no run yorker pushed into the covers
McCullum to White, 1 run full and driven to long on
McCullum to Clarke, 1 run comes down the track and works it to mid on and he takes a well judged single
McCullum to White, no run short and cut off the bottom edge into the ground and over the keeper
McCullum to White, no run flatter and driven off the inside edge to mid wicket
Guptill to Clarke, 1 run too straight and worked through the leg side to the sweeper
Guptill to White, no run tossed up and pushed back along the pitch
Guptill to White, FOUR runs tossed up again and White lofts it nicely over the bowlers' head for four. Nice stroke
Guptill to White, no run flatter this time and he tries to elevate again but doesn't quite get it and it bounces in front of mid off
Guptill to White, no run driven firmly to mid off
Guptill to White, SIX runs tossed up and White launches it straight bakc over the bowlers' head for a maximum and that's the game. Well played Australia.
This is Marc Ellison signing off. Goodluck and god speed.
